      "content": "Hey, I need you to draft a KYC (Know Your Customer) compliance memo for a new high-net-worth client we're onboarding. It's a bit of a mess, but the Audit & Compliance department is using a new automated scanning tool to check these memos, and it's super strict. If the scanner doesn't see the specific regulatory terminology it's looking for, it rejects the whole thing immediately. It's a huge pain.\n\nCan you make sure you address all the standard requirements: beneficial ownership, source of wealth/funds, PEP (Politically Exposed Person) status, enhanced due diligence (EDD), risk profiling, and AML (Anti-Money Laundering) protocols? \n\nHere is the client info:\n- Name: Julian Vane\n- Occupation: Private Equity Fund Manager\n- Primary Assets: Real estate holdings in UAE, various offshore shell companies (needs verification), art collection.\n- Source of Wealth: Divestment from tech startups in 2018, dividends from private equity.\n\nJust make sure the memo is thorough and covers all those regulatory bases so the scanner gives us the green light.",
